SIMPLE: utricle
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Utricle
<hw>U"tri*cle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>utriculus</ets> a little womb, a calycle, dim. of <ets>uter</ets>,
<ets>utris</ets>, a bag or bottle made of an animal's hide: cf. F.
<ets>utricule</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>A little sac or vesicle, as the air cell of fucus,
or seaweed.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>A microscopic cell in the
structure of an egg, animal, or plant.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A small, thin-walled, one-seeded
fruit, as of goosefoot.</def> <rj><au>Gray.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>A utriculus.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Utricular</ent>⟦br⟧
